Create new variable with different options in the prehospital treatment pathway

Normally, guidelines suggest a stepwise treatment of SE (2 BZD, AED, CI). Given that, we will try to find what patients are in each step, combining the medication given by caregivers and by EMS.

However, we could have patients outside this algorithm of treatment. We tried to find the patients who did not match in the previous groups (for example, patients who had more than 2 BZD by caregivers (home), patients who had more than 2 BZD in total in EMS rather than AED, patients who had AED in EMS without 2 BZD previously, patients ho had AED at home).

# Now, create new variable "prehospital" with different options in the prehospital treatment pathway.
# These are the categories that the variable "prehospital" will have, from 0 to 15:

# 0 = caregivers0 + EMS0  -> 0 total   # 18 patients
# 1 = caregivers0 + EMS1  -> 1 total   # 22 patients
# 2 = caregivers0 + EMS2  -> 2 total  # 8 patients
# 3 = caregivers0 + EMS3  -> 3 total  # 3 patients
# 4 = caregivers0 + EMS4  -> 4 total  # 1 patients
# 5 = caregivers0 + EMS5  -> 5 total  # 1 patients

# 6 = caregivers1 + EMS0  -> 1 total  # 5 patients
# 7 = caregivers1 + EMS1  -> 2 total  # 8 patients
# 8 = caregivers1 + EMS2  -> 3 total  # 4 patients
# 9 = caregivers1 + EMS3  -> 4 total  # 3 patients

# 10  = caregivers2 + EMS0  -> 2 total  # 4 patients
# 11 = caregivers2 + EMS1  -> 3 total  # 5 patients
# 12 = caregivers2 + EMS2  -> 4 total  # 1 patients

# 13 = caregivers3 + EMS0  -> 3 total  # 0 patients
# 14 = caregivers3 + EMS1  -> 4 total  # 1 patients
# 15 = caregivers3 + EMS2  -> 5 total  # 1 patients



pSERG$prehospital <- NA

pSERG$prehospital <- ifelse(pSERG$caregivers == 0 & !pSERG$BZDLOCATION.0 == "EMS", 0, NA)
pSERG$prehospital <- ifelse(pSERG$caregivers == 0 & pSERG$BZDLOCATION.0 == "EMS", 1, pSERG$prehospital)
pSERG$prehospital <- ifelse(pSERG$caregivers == 0 & pSERG$BZDLOCATION.0 == "EMS" & pSERG$BZDLOCATION.1 == "EMS", 2, pSERG$prehospital)

Once we have the treatment given to our patients well-defined, we would like to create some groups depending on the treatment given by caregivers and EMS (all the prehospital variable options: 0 BZD caregivers and 0 BZD EMS, 1 BZD caregivers and 0 BZD EMS, 2 BZD caregivers and 0 BZD EMS, etc.).
We would like to know the elapsed time from seizure onset to EMS arrival (Tc = EMSARRIVAL= time within the care of by caregivers), the time within the care of by EMS (tEMS = timeinambulance), and the time from seizure onset to hospital arrival (Ttotal= HOSPITALARRIVAL) of these patients in these groups.

# Create a database from pSERG with only the needed variables for the plots
alluvial <- pSERG[ , c("atrisk", "caregivers", "EMS", "total", "priorSE", "priorepilepsy")]

# Add the variable frequency of observations for the plots
alluvial$freq <- 85

# Change the name of the categories for the variable atrisk for the plots
alluvial$atrisk <- ifelse(alluvial$atrisk == "1", "yes", "no")

# Change the order of the variables of the database for the plots
alluvial <- alluvial[c("atrisk", "caregivers", "EMS", "total", "freq", "priorSE", "priorepilepsy")]



# Plot the diagrams:


# Diagram without color. 
alluvial( alluvial[1:85,1:4], freq=alluvial$freq, border= NA, col= "gray")

# Red: patients who arrived to the hospital without treatment.
alluvial( alluvial[1:85,1:4], freq=alluvial$freq, border= NA, 
              col=ifelse( alluvial$total == 0, "red", "gray"))

# Blue: patients at risk.
alluvial( alluvial[1:85,1:4], freq=alluvial$freq, border=NA, 
              col=ifelse( alluvial$atrisk == "yes", "Steelblue", "gray"))

# Green: patients with prior SE.
alluvial( alluvial[1:85,1:4], freq=alluvial$freq, border=NA, 
              col=ifelse( alluvial$priorSE == 1, "forestgreen", "gray"))

# Orange: patients with prior epilepsy.
alluvial( alluvial[1:85,1:4], freq=alluvial$freq, border=NA, 
              col=ifelse( alluvial$priorepilepsy == 1, "orange", "gray"))

# Create censtotal for the 1st BZD (1 if event before hospital arrival and within the first 60 min from SE onset, 0 censored). 
pSERG$censh <- pSERG$HOSPITALARRIVAL - pSERG$BZDTIME.0 
summary(pSERG$censh)
##     Min.  1st Qu.   Median     Mean  3rd Qu.     Max. 
## -1535.00     3.00    19.00    10.84    38.00   845.00
pSERG$censtotal <- ifelse(pSERG$censh > 0 & pSERG$BZDTIME.0 <= 60, 1, 0)
table(pSERG$censtotal)
## 
##  0  1 
## 24 61
# Create variable time to event or censoring
pSERG$BZDtimeKM <- NA
pSERG$BZDtimeKM <- ifelse(pSERG$censtotal == 1, pSERG$BZDTIME.0, NA)
summary(pSERG$BZDtimeKM)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.    NA's 
##    0.00    5.00   12.00   13.93   21.00   55.00      24

# Figure time to first BZD (entire cohort)
plot(survfit(Surv(pSERG$BZDtimeKM, pSERG$censtotal) ~ 1), fun = "event", 
     conf.int = FALSE, mark.time = TRUE, xlim = c(0, 60), ylim = c(0, 1), col = "blue", lwd = 3, 
     cex.axis = 1, cex.lab = 1,
     xlab="Time to first BZD (min)", ylab="Cum. prob. having received first BZD")

Line chart with time intervals under caregiver and EMS care before the time to first BZD

# Prepare variables for the plot

 # 0 = seizure onset
 # 0-t1 = time within the care of caregiver, which ends when EMS arrival or when caregiver gives RM
 # t1-t2 = if not BZD administered, time within the care of EMS until first BZD administered or hospital arrival (or final figure, 60 minutes, censored/truncated line)
 # Square means first BZD, circle means censored patient (hospital arrival or > 60 minutes in total)

  
  # Create variable to define intervals
pSERG$caregiverforplot <- pSERG$EMSARRIVAL
pSERG$caregiverforplot <- ifelse(pSERG$EMSARRIVAL > 59, 60, pSERG$caregiverforplot)
pSERG$caregiverforplot <- ifelse(pSERG$BZDtimeKM < pSERG$EMSARRIVAL, pSERG$BZDtimeKM, pSERG$caregiverforplot)


   # Give a number to each patient and order based on first time interval for a more organized plot 
pSERG$Patient <- 1:nrow(pSERG)
pSERG$Patiento <- factor(x = pSERG$Patient, levels = order(pSERG$caregiverforplot, decreasing = TRUE))

   # Convert to factor for the plot
pSERG$censtotal <- as.character(as.numeric(pSERG$censtotal))
pSERG$censtotal <- as.factor(as.character(pSERG$censtotal))



# LINE CHART with at-risk patient (A)

ggplot(pSERG[which(pSERG$atrisk == 1),], aes(x = Patiento)) + 
    # Plot gray line representing time from 0 to t1
    geom_linerange(aes(ymin = 0, ymax = caregiverforplot, colour="gray30")) + 
    # Plot red line representing time from t1 to t2
    geom_linerange(aes(ymin = caregiverforplot+ 0.1, ymax = BZDtimeKM, colour="brown2")) +
    # Plot points representing event or censoring
   geom_point(aes(y=BZDtimeKM, colour=factor(censtotal), shape=factor(censtotal))) +
    # Flip coordinates
    coord_flip() + 
    # Customize image, colors, legend, labels, and axis
  scale_color_manual(name= "", values = c("limegreen", "dodgerblue1", "brown2","gray30"),   labels = c("censored / truncated", "First BZD", "EMS care", "Caregiver care"))+
    scale_shape_manual(values = c(19, 15)) +
    guides(shape=FALSE, color=guide_legend(reverse = TRUE)) +
      labs(y = "Time to first BZD (min)", x="At-risk patients", tag = "A") + 
     theme_bw() + theme(panel.border = element_blank(), legend.position = c(0.8, 0.8),        legend.background= element_blank()) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60), expand = c(0, 0.1)) +
    scale_x_discrete(labels=NULL)

# LINE CHART with patients without risk (B)

ggplot(pSERG[which(pSERG$atrisk == 0),], aes(x = Patiento)) + 
    # Plot gray line representing time from 0 to t1
    geom_linerange(aes(ymin = 0, ymax = caregiverforplot, colour="gray30")) + 
    # Plot red line representing time from t1 to t2
    geom_linerange(aes(ymin = caregiverforplot+ 0.1, ymax = BZDtimeKM, colour="brown2")) +
    # Plot points representing event or censoring
   geom_point(aes(y=BZDtimeKM, colour=factor(censtotal), shape=factor(censtotal))) +
    # Flip coordinates
    coord_flip() + 
    # Customize image, colors, legend, labels, and axis
   scale_color_manual(name= "", values = c("limegreen", "dodgerblue1", "brown2","gray30"),    labels = c("censored / truncated", "First BZD", "EMS care", "Caregiver care"))+
      scale_shape_manual(values = c(19, 15)) +
    guides(shape=FALSE, color=guide_legend(reverse = TRUE)) +
